Class NfsResponseBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.ecs.nfsclient.rpc.RpcResponse
      • com.emc.ecs.nfsclient.nfs.NfsResponseBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NfsAccessResponse, NfsCommitResponse, NfsCreateResponse, NfsFsInfoResponse, NfsFsStatResponse, NfsGetAttrResponse, NfsLinkResponse, NfsLookupResponse, NfsMkdirResponse, NfsMknodResponse, NfsPathconfResponse, NfsReaddirplusResponse, NfsReaddirResponse, NfsReadlinkResponse, NfsReadResponse, NfsRemoveResponse, NfsRenameResponse, NfsRmdirResponse, NfsSetAttrResponse, NfsSymlinkResponse, NfsWriteResponse

    public abstract class NfsResponseBase
extends RpcResponse
    The base class for all NFS responses specified by RFC 1813 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1813).

      • getAttributes

        public final NfsGetAttributes getAttributes()
        Returns:
        File system object post-operation attributes. These are provided for many calls. For information on the object to which the attributes refer, or for other details, see RFC 1813 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1813).

      • getFileHandle

        public final byte[] getFileHandle()
        Returns:
        The file handle for the system object that was created for a successful CREATE, MKDIR, MKNOD, or SYMLINK request, or looked up for a LOOKUP request. This is null for all other requests, and also for failed requests.

      • stateIsOk

        public boolean stateIsOk()
        Check the state returned in the response. For details, see RFC 1813 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1813).
        Returns:
        true if the state is NFS3_OK, false otherwise
